results.name: Number of partitions of n into 4 summands a>=b>=c>=d>0 with integer a/b, b/c and c/d.
formula: a(n) = Sum_{d|n, d>1} A122935(d-1). - _Franklin T. Adams-Watters_, Sep 20 2006
example: a(36)=20 because there are 20 partitions of 36 in 4 summands a>=b>=c>=d>0 with integer a/b, b/c and c/d:
xref: Cf. A026810 = number of partitions of n into exactly 4 parts.
